    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.26.56-57_0001"/>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">56</fw>
                
                <fw type="letterhead">
                    <hi rend="caps">MID-WEST SILVER LAKE
                        <lb/>
                    WRITERS CONFERENCE</hi>
                        <lb/>
                    Oak Haven, Route Three
                        <lb/>
                    Fairmont, Minnesota 
                </fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>3/3/58</dateline>
                
                    <salute>Dr John <hi rend="caps">G</hi> Neihardt</salute>
                    <salute>Mein Sehr Geherter Herr,</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>Publicity for our July 23-28 Conference is in full swing. I <add>have</add> heard of two of your students; Prof Lem<del>m</del>on<add>s</add> of Eau Claire Teachers College, Wisc, wrote me he would try to come,- his wife is expecting a baby in July.</p>
                
                <p>Because of our special effort this year on account of Minnesota's Centennial y<add>e</add>ar it would be fitting to ask as many as possible among your students to come and greet you.</p>
                
                <p>So if you will send me some names of former students that will help greatly.</p>
                
                <p>Fred Manfred author of Lord Grizzley has been invited: I called on him personally. He has a marvelous viewed home built on a cliff overlooking the Minnesota River Valley, a valley almost depopulated by the Indian Wars of the '60's</p>
                
                <p>The State Historical Society director has asked me to offer a public lecture <del>o</del><add>i</add>n this area,- I am confining it to the Silver Lake and Spirit Lake Pioneer Days.</p>
                
                <p>Directo<add>r</add> Russell Fridley of the Society above has agreed to come here in April to visit nearby historical scoiety leaders for the purpose of inviting them to our Jily<sic>July</sic> 23-28 meeting.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Believe me,</salute>
                    <salute>Most earnestly and fraternally yours,</salute>
                    <signed>P Evans Coleman</signed>
                    <signed>P Evans Coleman, Ph D</signed>
                </closer>
                
            </div1>
            
            
